1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Ever notice how a BMW suddenly sounds meaner

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:06,000
in sport mode? That’s not just your imagination.

3
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:09,000
In sport mode, BMW changes how the car

4
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:12,000
behaves. The throttle gets sharper, the transmission holds

5
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,000
gears longer, and the engine revs higher before

6
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:18,000
shifting. That means you hear more of the

7
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:21,000
engine’s natural sound. On many BMWs, the sound

8
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:24,000
changes even more because the car plays enhanced

9
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:27,000
engine noise through the speakers. So some of

10
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:30,000
that aggressive growl is real, and some of

11
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,000
it is tuned in. The result is simple:

12
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:36,000
sport mode makes the car feel faster, louder,

13
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:39,000
and more alive. BMW doesn’t just go faster

14
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:42,000
in sport mode. It talks back.
